The intermittent data connectivity issues experienced on the MTN network Thursday morning have been resolved and mobile data has now been restored the company said.Earlier on Thursday the mobile operator announced that the intermittent network disruption across the country affected data services and said the company s engineers were working fervently to restore connectivity.Voice services were not affected.In an updated statement the company said some of its enterprise customers were still experiencing connectivity challenges. Our engineers are working hard to bring them back online. 